==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waistcloth
<hw>Waist"cloth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
cloth or wrapper worn about the waist; by extension, such a garment worn
about the hips and passing between the thighs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A covering of canvas or tarpaulin
for the hammocks, stowed on the nettings, between the quarterdeck and
the forecastle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waistcoat</ent>⟦br⟧
